HEADWORD: Sulphostannic
<hw>Sul`pho*stan"nic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, a sulphacid of tin (more exactly
called <xex>metasulphostannic acid</xex>), which is obtained as a dark
brown amorphous substance, H<?/SnS<?/, forming a well-known series of
salts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

